Hochtief Airport Unit Has Five Bidders Left, Platow Brief Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-06-28T20:19:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/hochtief-airport-unit-has-five-bidders-left-platow-brief-says.html
Hochtief AG (HOT) ’s airport-operating unit
has five bidders left in the running and offers are valued at
about 1.5 billion euros ($2.2 billion), Platow Brief reported,
without saying how it got the information.  The bidders are  Vinci SA (DG) , Fraport AG in cooperation with
 Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ’s RREEF division,  Allianz SE (ALV)  together with
Global Infrastructure Partners, as well as the operators of the
Shanghai and Singapore Changi airports, according to Platow.
Binding offers are expected within three weeks, the publication
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  